\f1 ; {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Traditional_Chinese_characters"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 traditional Chinese}}: 
\f3 \'c0\'73\'be\'f0
\f1 ; {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pinyin"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 pinyin}}: 
\f4\i L\'f3ngsh\'f9
\f1\i0 ; {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_Tibetan_language"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Standard Tibetan}}: mGon-po Klu-grub) was an Indian {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahayana"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Mah\uc0\u257 y\u257 na Buddhist}} thinker, scholar-saint and philosopher. He is widely considered one of the most important Buddhist philosophers.{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nagarjuna#cite_note-Garfield-2"}}{\fldrslt 
